addEntry(address,string).details: CIDs must be base58-encoded in order to work with this function

params._addr: The Ethereum address of the entry to add to the registry
params._cid: The IPFS hash of the entry to add to the registry

allowRecoverability(address).details: By default deriving from AragonApp makes it recoverable

params.token: Token address that would be recovered

allowRecoverability(address).return: bool whether the app allows the recovery

canPerform(address,bytes32,uint256[]).details: Check whether an action can be performed by a sender for a particular role on this app
canPerform(address,bytes32,uint256[]).return: Boolean indicating whether the sender has the permissions to perform the action.        Always returns false if the app hasn't been initialized yet.

getEntry(address).details: getter for the entries mapping to IPFS data

params._addr: The Ethereum address of the entry to get

getEntry(address).return: contentId pointing to the IPFS structured content object for the entry

getEntryIndex(address).details: getter for the entries mapping for an index in entryArr

params._addr: The Ethereum address of the entry to get

getEntryIndex(address).return: contentId pointing to the IPFS structured content object for the entry

getInitializationBlock().return: Block number in which the contract was initialized

getRecoveryVault().details: Get the recovery vault for the app
getRecoveryVault().return: Recovery vault address for the app

hasInitialized().return: Whether the contract has been initialized by the time of the current block

initialize().details: Initializes the app, this is the Aragon custom constructor

removeEntry(address,string).details: this function only supports CIDs that are base58-encoded

params._addr: The Ethereum address of the entry to remove from the registry
params._cid: The IPFS hash of the entry to remove from the registry; used only for radspec here

params._token: Token balance to be sent to recovery vault.

updateEntry(address,string,string).details: this function only supports CIDs that are base58-encoded

params._addr: The Ethereum address of the entry to update
params._newCid: The new IPFS hash containing the metadata of the entry
params._oldCid: The current IPFS hash containing the metadata of the entry

addEntry(address,string).notice: Add `_addr` to the registry with metadata `_cid`

getEntry(address).notice: Get data associated to entry `_addr` from the registry.

getEntryIndex(address).notice: Get index associated to entry `_addr` from the registry.

isEntryAdded(address).notice: Checks if `_entry` exists in the registry

removeEntry(address,string).notice: Remove `_addr` from the registry with metadata `_cid`

transferToVault(address).notice: Send funds to recovery Vault. This contract should never receive funds,        but in case it does, this function allows one to recover them.

updateEntry(address,string,string).notice: Update `_addr` from current metadata `_oldCid` to new metadata `_newCid`
